Power and Type I error of One Sample t test

Benedict Kongyir

11/08/2023

rm(list = ls())
setwd("D:/Research_Fall2023/Pretest-Simulation/Power and Type I error Rate/Results")
set.seed(1)
N <- 100000
alpha <- 0.05
d <- 0.5
sample_size <- c(10,20,30,40,50,60)
#power of SW test
Power_SW_exp <-Power_SW_unif <- Power_SW_t <- Power_SW_chisq <- Power_SW_gamma <- Power_SW_weibull <- Power_SW_logn <- Power_SW_contaminate <- Power_SW_q<- numeric(length(sample_size))
#Type I error
Type1Error_Norm <- Type1Error_exp <-Type1Error_unif <- Type1Error_t <- Type1Error_chisq <- Type1Error_gamma <- Type1Error_weibull <- Type1Error_logn <-Type1Error_contaminate <- Type1Error_q<- numeric(length(sample_size))
#inflation of Type I error
InflationType1Error_exp <-InflationType1Error_unif <- InflationType1Error_t <- InflationType1Error_chisq <- InflationType1Error_gamma <- InflationType1Error_weibull <- InflationType1Error_logn <- InflationType1Error_contaminate <- InflationType1Error_q<- numeric(length(sample_size))
#Power of t test
Power_ttest_Norm <- Power_ttest_exp <-Power_ttest_unif <- Power_ttest_t <- Power_ttest_chisq <- Power_ttest_gamma <- Power_ttest_weibull <- Power_ttest_logn <- Power_ttest_contaminate <- Power_ttest_q<- numeric(length(sample_size))
#powerloss
powrloss_exp <-powrloss_unif  <-powrloss_gamma <-powrloss_beta <-powrloss_chisq <-powrloss_t <- powrloss_weibull <- powrloss_logn <- powrloss_contaminate <-powrloss_q<- numeric(length(sample_size))
for( i in 1 : length(sample_size)){
  n <- sample_size[i]
print(n)
PowrSW_exp <- PowrSW_unif <- PowrSW_t <- PowrSW_chisq <- PowrSW_gamma <- PowrSW_weibull <- PowrSW_logn <- PowrSW_contaminate <- PowrSW_q<- numeric(N)
error_ttest_norm <- error_ttest_exp <- error_ttest_unif <- error_ttest_t <- error_ttest_chisq <- error_ttest_gamma <- error_ttest_weibull<- error_ttest_logn <- error_ttest_contaminate <- error_ttest_q<- numeric(N)
powr_ttest_norm <- powr_ttest_exp <- powr_ttest_unif <- powr_ttest_t <- powr_ttest_chisq <- powr_ttest_gamma <- powr_ttest_weibull <- powr_ttest_logn<- powr_ttest_contaminate <- powr_ttest_q<- numeric(N)

 for(j in 1 : N){
   # normal distn
    n1 <- rnorm(n, mean = 0, sd = 1)
    if(t.test(n1)$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_norm[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test(n1 + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_norm[j] <- 1
    }
    # ===============================================================================================
    # e ~exp(theta),  E(X) = theta and VAR(X) = theta^2
    # ===============================================================================================
    e1 <- rexp(n, rate = 1)
    if(t.test(e1 - 1)$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_exp[j] <- 1
    }
    if(shapiro.test(e1)$p.value <= alpha){
      PowrSW_exp[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test(e1 -1 + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_exp[j] <- 1
    }
    # ===============================================================================================
    # u1 ~U(a, b),  E(X) = (a + b)/2 and VAR(X) = [(b-a)^2]/12
    # ===============================================================================================
    u1 <- runif(n, min = 0, max = 1)
    if(t.test((u1 - 0.5)/sqrt(1/12))$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_unif[j] <- 1
    } 
    if(shapiro.test(u1)$p.value <= alpha){
      PowrSW_unif[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test((u1-0.5)/sqrt(1/12) + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_unif[j] <- 1
    }
    # ===============================================================================================
    # t1 ~t_v,  E(X) = 0 for v >1 and VAR(X) = v/(v-2)
    # ===============================================================================================
    t1 <-rt(n, df = 3) 
    if(t.test((t1)/sqrt(3))$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_t[j] <- 1
    }
    if(shapiro.test(t1)$p.value <= alpha){
      PowrSW_t[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test((t1)/sqrt(3) + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_t[j] <- 1
    }
    # ===============================================================================================
    # k1 ~X_k,  E(X) = k and VAR(X) = 2k
    # ===============================================================================================
    k1 <-rchisq(n, df = 7) 
    if(t.test((k1 - 7)/sqrt(14))$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_chisq[j] <- 1
    }
    if(shapiro.test(k1)$p.value <= alpha){
      PowrSW_chisq[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test((k1 - 7)/sqrt(14) + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_chisq[j] <- 1
    }
    # ===============================================================================================
    # g1 ~gamma(alpha, beta), where beta = 1/theta so E(X) = alpha/theta and VAR(X) = alpha/(theta)^2
    # ===============================================================================================
    g1 <- rgamma(n, shape = 3, rate = 0.1) 
    if(t.test((g1-30)/sqrt(300))$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_gamma[j] <- 1
    }
    if(shapiro.test(g1)$p.value <= alpha){
      PowrSW_gamma[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test((g1-30)/sqrt(300) + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_gamma[j] <- 1
    }
    
    # ===============================================================================================
    # w1 ~Weibull(shape, scale)  E(X) = scale Gamma(1 + 1/shape) and 
    # VAR(X) = scale^2[Gamma(1 + 2/shape) - (Gamma(1 + 1/shape))^2]
    # ===============================================================================================
    w1 <- rweibull(n, shape = 1, scale = 2) 
    u <- (w1-2*gamma(2))/sqrt(4*(gamma(3) - gamma(2)))
    
    if(t.test(u)$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_weibull[j] <- 1
    }
    if(shapiro.test(w1)$p.value <= alpha){
      PowrSW_weibull[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test(u + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_weibull[j] <- 1
    }
    # ===================================================================================================
    # l1 ~lognormal(mu, sigma^2)  E(X) = exp(mu + sigma^2/2) VAR(X) = [exp(sigma^2)-1]exp(2mu + sigma^2)
    # ===================================================================================================
    l1 <- rlnorm(n, meanlog = 0, sdlog = 1)
    
    z1 <- (l1- exp(0+1/2))/sqrt(sqrt((exp(1)-1)*exp(2*0 + 1)))
  
    if(t.test(z1)$p.value <= alpha){
      error_ttest_logn[j] <- 1
    }
    if(shapiro.test(l1)$p.value <= alpha){
      PowrSW_logn[j] <- 1
    }
    if(t.test(z1 + d)$p.value <= alpha){
      powr_ttest_logn[j] <- 1
    }
    
    # ===================================================================================================
    #  X~contaminated   E(X) = 0, VAR(X) = 25
    # ===================================================================================================
      b=rbinom(n,1,0.65)
      cont=b*rnorm(n,0,1)+(1-b)*rnorm(n,0,5)
      
    if(t.test(cont)$p.value <= alpha){
          error_ttest_contaminate[j] <- 1
        }
        if(shapiro.test(cont)$p.value <= alpha){
          PowrSW_contaminate[j] <- 1
        }
        if(t.test(cont/5 + d)$p.value <= alpha){
          powr_ttest_contaminate[j] <- 1
        }
      
    # ===================================================================================================
    #  h and g distribution 
    # ===================================================================================================
      g = 0.2 ; h = 0.4
       q <- (exp(g*rnorm(n)) - 1)/g*exp(0.5*h*(rnorm(n))^2)
      
       mean_q <- (exp(g^2/(2-2*h)-1))/(g*(1-h)^0.5)
       var_q <- (1-2*exp(g^2/(2-4*h)) + exp(2*g^2/(1-2*h)))/(g^2*(1-2*h)^0.5) - mean_q^2
       
    if(t.test((q - mean_q)/sqrt(var_q))$p.value <= alpha){
          error_ttest_q[j] <- 1
        }
        if(shapiro.test(q)$p.value <= alpha){
          PowrSW_q[j] <- 1
        }
        if(t.test((q - mean_q)/sqrt(var_q) + d)$p.value <= alpha){
          powr_ttest_q[j] <- 1
        }
      
 }


  ##Type I error
  Type1Error_Norm[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_norm), 3)
  Type1Error_exp[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_exp), 3)
  Type1Error_unif[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_unif), 3)
  Type1Error_t[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_t), 3)
  Type1Error_chisq[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_chisq), 3)
  Type1Error_gamma[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_gamma), 3)
  Type1Error_weibull[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_weibull), 3)
  Type1Error_logn[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_logn), 3)
  Type1Error_contaminate[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_contaminate), 3)
  Type1Error_q[i] <- round(mean(error_ttest_q), 3)
  #inflation of Type I error
  InflationType1Error_exp[i] <- Type1Error_exp[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_unif[i] <- Type1Error_unif[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_t[i] <- Type1Error_t[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_chisq[i] <- Type1Error_chisq[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_gamma[i] <- Type1Error_gamma[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_weibull[i] <- Type1Error_weibull[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_logn[i] <- Type1Error_logn[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_contaminate[i] <- Type1Error_contaminate[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  InflationType1Error_q[i] <- Type1Error_q[i] - Type1Error_Norm[i]
  #power of SW test
  Power_SW_exp[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_exp), 3)
  Power_SW_unif[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_unif), 3)
  Power_SW_t[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_t), 3)
  Power_SW_chisq[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_chisq), 3)
  Power_SW_gamma[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_gamma), 3)
  Power_SW_weibull[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_weibull), 3)
  Power_SW_logn[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_logn), 3)
  Power_SW_contaminate[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_contaminate), 3)
  Power_SW_q[i] <- round(mean(PowrSW_q), 3)
  # Power of t test
  Power_ttest_Norm[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_norm), 3)
  Power_ttest_exp[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_exp), 3)
  Power_ttest_unif[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_unif), 3)
  Power_ttest_t[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_t), 3)
  Power_ttest_chisq[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_chisq), 3)
  Power_ttest_gamma[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_gamma), 3)
  Power_ttest_weibull[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_weibull), 3)
  Power_ttest_logn[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_logn), 3)
  Power_ttest_contaminate[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_contaminate), 3)
  Power_ttest_q[i] <- round(mean(powr_ttest_q), 3)
  #Powerloss of t test
  powrloss_exp[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_exp[i]
  powrloss_unif[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_unif[i]
  powrloss_t[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_t[i]
  powrloss_chisq[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_chisq[i]
  powrloss_gamma[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_gamma[i]
  powrloss_weibull[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_weibull[i]
  powrloss_logn[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_logn[i]
  powrloss_contaminate[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_contaminate[i]
  powrloss_q[i] <- Power_ttest_Norm[i] - Power_ttest_q[i]
}

lines(sample_size, powrloss_unif, lwd= 2, col = "blue")
lines(sample_size, powrloss_t,lwd= 2, col = "gold")
lines(sample_size, powrloss_chisq, lwd= 2,col = "green")
lines(sample_size, powrloss_gamma, lwd= 2,col = "pink")
lines(sample_size, powrloss_weibull, lwd= 2,col = "brown")
lines(sample_size, powrloss_logn, lwd= 2,col = "orange")
lines(sample_size, powrloss_contaminate, lwd= 2,col = "purple")
lines(sample_size, powrloss_q, lwd= 2,col = "cyan")
abline(h = 0)
title(main = "Power loss of t test.")
legend("topright", legend=c("expontial", "uniform", "t", "chisq", "gamma", "weibull", "lognormal", "contaminate", "g and h"),
       col=c( "red","blue", "gold", "green", "pink", "brown", "orange","purple", "cyan"), lty =1,cex = 0.5)

0.0.6 Utility of SW test(Lognormal Distribution)

## add extra space to right margin of plot within frame
par(mar=c(5, 4, 4, 6) + 0.1)

## Plot first set of data and draw its axis
plot(sample_size, Power_SW_logn, pch=16, axes=FALSE, ylim=c(0,1), xlab="", ylab="", 
   type="b",col="black", main="Utility of Shapiro Wilk test")
axis(2, ylim=c(0,1),col="black",las=1)  ## las=1 makes horizontal labels
mtext("Power of SW test",side=2,line=2.5)
box()

## Allow a second plot on the same graph
par(new=TRUE)

## Plot the second plot and put axis scale on right
plot(sample_size, powrloss_logn, pch=15,  xlab="", ylab="", ylim=c(0,0.5), 
    axes=FALSE, type="b", col="red")
mtext("Power loss of t test",side=4,col="red",line=4) 
axis(4, ylim=c(0,0.5), col="red",col.axis="red",las=1)

lines(sample_size, InflationType1Error_logn, pch=11,  xlab="", ylab="", ylim=c(0,0.5), 
     type="b", col="blue")
## a little farther out (line=4) to make room for labels
axis(4, ylim=c(0,0.5), col="red",col.axis="red",las=1)

## Draw the time axis
axis(1,pretty(range(sample_size),10))
mtext("Sample Size",side=1,col="black",line=2.5)  

## Add Legend
legend("right",legend=c("Power of SW test","Power loss of t test", "Inflation of Type I error"),
  text.col=c("black","red", "blue"),pch=c(16,15, 11),col=c("black","red", "blue"))
